textAnnotations.description:
So he put up for the night at The Admiral's Head, that
famous Portsmouth hostelry, secand only in historic
interest to the George, unhappily destroyed by German
lombes during the last war. Having deposited his
baggage and unpacked his overnight-boz he
went in search of a drink. The lower bar was
empty, save for the lady known by all habitue
* ?25 as 'Seaweed', and a youngish, sharp-eyed
man who was storing moodily into a gin
and tanic.
